{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17619307","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17619307"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:30:30+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:30:30+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16551"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16551","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16551"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.49,0.11,0.23,0.11]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9242"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65663"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9242","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9242"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16551"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51102"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6677"},{"type":"tags","id":"7114"},{"type":"tags","id":"7162"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21899"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21902"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65663","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65663"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe vertebrobasilar system is an important component of cerebral blood supply.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the terminal branches of the vertebrobasilar system?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Anterior cerebral artery","Posterior cerebral artery","Middle cerebral artery","Posterior communicating artery","Ophthalmic artery"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe vertebrobasilar system is formed by the union of the two vertebral arteries to form the basilar artery. The basilar artery terminates by dividing into two \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior cerebral arteries\u003C/strong\u003E (PCAs). The PCAs supply the occipital lobes (visual cortex) and inferior temporal lobes, which explains why PCA territory strokes often present with homonymous hemianopia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior cerebral arteries\u003C/strong\u003E are branches of the internal carotid arteries and supply the medial aspects of the frontal and parietal lobes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emiddle cerebral arteries\u003C/strong\u003E are the largest branches of the internal carotid arteries and supply most of the lateral surface of the cerebral hemispheres\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior communicating arteries\u003C/strong\u003E connect the internal carotid arteries to the posterior cerebral arteries, forming part of the Circle of Willis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eophthalmic artery\u003C/strong\u003E is the first branch of the internal carotid artery and supplies the eye and surrounding structures\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding this vascular anatomy is crucial for localising strokes and other cerebrovascular events.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The vertebrobasilar system terminates by dividing into two posterior cerebral arteries.","The posterior cerebral arteries supply the occipital lobes and inferior temporal lobes.","The vertebrobasilar system is formed by the union of the vertebral arteries to form the basilar artery."],"references":["Wake-Buck AK, Gatenby JC, Gore JC. Hemodynamic characteristics of the vertebrobasilar system analyzed using MRI-based models. PLoS One. 2012;7(12):e51346. doi: 10.1371/journal.pone.0051346. Epub 2012 Dec 10. PMID: 23251503; PMCID: PMC3519605.","Schoen JC, Boysen MM, Warren CR, Chakravarthy B, Lotfipour S. Vertebrobasilar artery occlusion. West J Emerg Med. 2011 May;12(2):233-9. PMID: 21691534; PMCID: PMC3099615.","Hall, J. E., \u0026 Hall, M. E. (2020). Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology E-Book: Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Singh, V. (2024).\u00a0Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022).\u00a0The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51102"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16551"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51102","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51102"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-26T17:00:09+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-31T14:36:19+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9242"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65663"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups"